Franklin T. Hanshar is currently a M.Sc. student in the Department of Computing and Information Science at the University of Guelph, Ontario, Canada. He received a B.Sc. degree in Computer Science from Brock University in 2005. His research interests include uncertain reasoning, optimization and evolutionary computation. Beatrice Ombuki-Berman is currently an Associate Professor in the Department of Computer Science at Brock University, Ontario, Canada. She obtained a PhD and ME in Information Engineering from University of The Ryukyus, Okinawa, Japan in 2001 and 1998, respectively. She received a B.Sc. in Mathematics and Computer Science from Jomo Kenyatta University, Nairobi, Kenya. Her primary research interest is evolutionary computation and applied optimization. Other research interests include neural networks, machine learning and ant colony optimization.